    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>247. Memorandum From the <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to
                    the Secretary of Defense (<persName corresp="#p_WCE1" type="to"
                        >Wilson</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d247fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SP1">S/P</gloss>–<gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 62 D 1, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 5519 Series. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">19 August 1955</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Revised Force Bases for Vietnam.</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Reference is made to: <list>
                            <label>a.</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_ChMAAG1">ChMAAG</gloss>, Indochina message MG 742
                                A, <gloss target="#t_DTG1">DTG</gloss> 091330Z August 1955.<note
                                    n="2" xml:id="d247fn2">
                                    <ref target="#d241">Document 241</ref>.</note>
                            </item>
                            <label>b.</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> message <gloss
                                    target="#t_DTG1">DTG</gloss> 102223Z August 1955.<note n="3"
                                    xml:id="d247fn3">
                                    <ref target="#d242">Document 242</ref>.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>This memorandum is in response to the memorandum by the Acting Assistant
                        Secretary of Defense (<gloss target="#t_ISA1">ISA</gloss>), subject as
                        above, dated 29 July 1955,<note n="4" xml:id="d247fn4">
                            <ref target="#d239">Document 239</ref>.</note> in which he requested the
                        views of the Joint Chiefs of Staff on the Country Team, Indochina’s
                        recommendation to increase the force bases for Vietnam, and, in so doing,
                        consider and present views on six specific points.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>The Joint Chiefs of Staff have reviewed the comments and recommendations
                        of <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> contained in the message
                        referred to in subparagraph 1 b above concerning this matter. They consider
                        that <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> has correctly assessed the
                        situation in South Vietnam and has adequately answered the six points raised
                        in your memorandum. The Joint Chiefs of Staff recommend that the force bases
                        proposed by the Country Team, Indochina, be supported through <gloss
                            target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1956, with a review of the force bases for
                            <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1957 to be made at a later
                        date.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>In view of the presently limited funds available for <gloss
                            target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> in <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss>
                        1956, the Joint Chiefs of Staff consider that approval of the foregoing
                        recommended action should be contingent on obtaining the additional funds
                        required for an increase to South Vietnamese forces from sources other than
                            <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> end-item matériel and Direct
                        Forces Support funds.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>For the Joint Chiefs of Staff:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RAAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Arthur Radford</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chairman<lb/>Joint Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
